content.text:
### List User Accounts with Better Auth Client

Source: https://github.com/better-auth/better-auth/blob/canary/docs/content/docs/concepts/users-accounts.mdx

Retrieve all accounts associated with the current user using the authClient.listAccounts() method. This returns authentication data for each provider connected to the user's account.

```typescript
import { authClient } from "@/lib/auth-client"

const accounts = await authClient.listAccounts();
```

--------------------------------

### Link Social Account to Existing User - Client and Server Side

Source: https://github.com/better-auth/better-auth/blob/canary/docs/content/docs/concepts/oauth.mdx

Connect a social provider account to an authenticated user's existing account. Client-side usage requires active session, while server-side requires authentication headers containing the user's session token.

```typescript
await authClient.linkSocial({
  provider: "google", // or any other provider id
})
```

```typescript
await auth.api.linkSocialAccount({
  body: {
    provider: "google", // or any other provider id
  },
  headers: await headers() // headers containing the user's session token
});
```

--------------------------------

### Link Social Provider Account with Basic Parameters

Source: https://github.com/better-auth/better-auth/blob/canary/docs/content/docs/concepts/users-accounts.mdx

Enable authenticated users to manually link their account to a social provider using the client-side linkSocial method. This initiates an OAuth flow that redirects to the provider and returns to the specified callback URL upon completion.

```typescript
import { authClient } from "@/lib/auth-client"

await authClient.linkSocial({
    provider: "google",
    callbackURL: "/callback"
});
```

--------------------------------

### Link Social Provider with Custom Scopes

Source: https://github.com/better-auth/better-auth/blob/canary/docs/content/docs/concepts/users-accounts.mdx

Link a social provider account while requesting specific OAuth scopes that may differ from initial authentication scopes. This allows users to grant additional permissions for newly linked accounts, such as Google Drive read-only access.

```typescript
import { authClient } from "@/lib/auth-client"

await authClient.linkSocial({
    provider: "google",
    callbackURL: "/callback",
    scopes: ["https://www.googleapis.com/auth/drive.readonly"]
});
```

--------------------------------

### Link Social Account Using ID Token

Source: https://github.com/better-auth/better-auth/blob/canary/docs/content/docs/concepts/users-accounts.mdx

Link a social provider account directly using an ID token without redirecting to the provider's OAuth flow. This approach is useful when tokens are already available from native SDKs, mobile apps, or custom OAuth implementations. Optional parameters include nonce, accessToken, and refreshToken depending on provider requirements.

```typescript
import { authClient } from "@/lib/auth-client"

await authClient.linkSocial({
    provider: "google",
    idToken: {
        token: "id_token_from_provider",
        nonce: "nonce_used_for_token",
        accessToken: "access_token",
        refreshToken: "refresh_token"
    }
});
```

